    en: "The Home Energy Assistance Program, or HEAP, pays part of heating and utility costs for income-eligible NY households. The federal authority is the Low Income Home Energy Assistance Act at 42 USC § 8621. NY OTDA runs the program through the county social services districts. There are four parts — Regular HEAP (winter), Emergency HEAP (imminent shutoff or fuel runout), Cooling Assistance (summer), and Heating Equipment Repair and Replacement. HEAP is not a loan — no repayment is required."
